Staff supervision and performance management
• Monitor staff performance and ensure that employees meet professional and organisational standards.
• Conduct periodic evaluations and provide feedback to improve productivity and service quality.
• Address professional conflicts and disciplinary issues when necessary.
Human resource policy and compliance
• Develop and implement HR policies, internal regulations, and staff guidelines.
• Ensure that employment contracts, working hours, and staff management practices comply with applicable
labour regulations.
